The paper deals with the problem of detecting morphing attacks on facial recognition systems, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of deep face representations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed algorithms on a large database of facial images suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
